HEADWORD: escarole
<hw>escarole</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Fr., from OFr.
<ets>scariole</ets>. fr. LL. <ets>escariola</ets>, L.
<ets>escarius</ets> of food, fit to eat, <ets>esca</ets> food, fr.
<ets>edere</ets> to eat.]</ety> <def>a variety of endive (<spn>Cichorium
endivia</spn>) often used in salads, having leaves with irregular
frilled edges.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> endive, curly endive.</syn>⟦br⟧
